choices"]," — Provide context for decision-making"],["li",{},["strong",{},"Design for habit formation"]," — Create satisfying interaction loops"]],["h2",{"id":"phase-3-prototyping-testing"},"Phase 3: Prototyping & Testing"],["p",{},"With the conceptual framework in place, I moved into the iterative cycle of prototyping and testing."],["h3",{"id":"low-fidelity-wireframes"},"Low-Fidelity Wireframes"],["p",{},"I created wireframes focusing on user flows and information hierarchy, deliberately keeping the visual design minimal to focus feedback on functionality and structure."],["h3",{"id":"user-testing-round-1"},"User Testing (Round 1)"],["p",{},"Testing wireframes with 8 participants revealed several key insights:"],["ul",{},["li",{},"Users wanted more immediate feedback when logging activities"],["li",{},"The impact visualization wasn't intuitive for most users"],["li",{},"People were confused by technical environmental terminology"]],["h3",{"id":"mid-fidelity-prototypes"},"Mid-Fidelity Prototypes"],["p",{},"Based on testing feedback, I refined the concept and developed interactive prototypes with more visual detail, focusing on:"],["ul",{},["li",{},"Simplified data visualization using familiar metaphors"],["li",{},"Immediate positive reinforcement for logged activities"],["li",{},"Progressive disclosure of more complex environmental information"]],["h3",{"id":"user-testing-round-2"},"User Testing (Round 2)"],["p",{},"A second round of testing showed significant improvements in usability, but highlighted new challenges:"],["ul",{},["li",{},"Users wanted to compare their impact with friends or community averages"],["li",{},"Weekly summaries were more motivating than daily statistics"],["li",{},"The onboarding process felt too lengthy"]],["h2",{"id":"phase-4-visual-design-refinement"},"Phase 4: Visual Design & Refinement"],["p",{},"With the core experience validated, I moved into high-fidelity visual design."],["h3",{"id":"visual-language"},"Visual Language"],["p",{},"